.TH "drm_dp_calc_pbn_mode" 9 "drm_dp_calc_pbn_mode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_dp_calc_pbn_mode \- Calculate the PBN for a mode.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_dp_calc_pbn_mode
.BI "(int clock "  ","
.BI "int bpp "  ","
.BI "bool dsc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "clock" 12
dot clock for the mode
.IP "bpp" 12
bpp for the mode.
.IP "dsc" 12
DSC mode. If true, bpp has units of 1/16 of a bit per pixel
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This uses the formula in the spec to calculate the PBN value for a mode.
